Class LabelMatcher

    public class LabelMatcher
extends AbstractComponentMatcher
    Matches an AWT or Swing Component by the text of the associated JLabel and (optionally) by type.
    Author:
    Alex Ruiz
    See Also:
    JLabel.getLabelFor(), JLabel.setLabelFor(Component)

    • Method Detail

      • matches

        @RunsInCurrentThread
public boolean matches(@Nullable
                                  java.awt.Component c)

        Indicates whether the given AWT or Swing Component matches the criteria specified in this matcher:

        1. the text of the JLabel attached to the Component to look for matches the text specified in this matcher
        2. the Component to look for is of the type specified in this matcher (if specified)
        3. visibility of the given Component matches the value specified in this matcher

        Note: This method is accessed in the current executing thread. Such thread may or may not be the event dispatch thread (EDT.) Client code must call this method from the EDT.

        Parameters:
        c - the Component to verify.
        Returns:
        true if the name and visibility of the given Component matches the values specified in this matcher, false otherwise.
